1) Install SSH Server 
Command :- sudo apt-get install openssh-server

2)To enable ssh service
Command :- sudo sysytemctl start ssh

3) Test ssh service by login into the sysytem
Command :- ssh kali@power9-bmc

4) Update and then install openssh-server
Command :- sudo apt update
Command :- sudo apt upgrade

5) Install openssh-server
Command :- sudo apt install openssh-server

6) Verify & run ssh service
Command :- sudo systemctl status ssh

7) Configure firewall and open port no 22
Command :- sudo ufw allow ssh
Command :- sudo ufw enable
Command :- sudo ufw status

8) To establish connection with own computer
Command :- ssh 127.0.0.1
